Let \[f(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl} ax + 4, & \text{ if } x > 3, \\
2x - 6, & \text{ if } -3 \leq x \leq 3, \\
bx^2 + 1, & \text{ if } x < -3.
\end{array}
\right.\] Determine the sum \(a + b\) such that the piecewise function \(f(x)\) is continuous at the points \(x = -3\) and \(x = 3\).

